{td rowspan=6 style="text-align: left;"}Environmental Monitoring and Control{/td}
{td}The system should monitor soil moisture in real time and trigger automated irrigation based on configurable thresholds.{/td}
{td}As a farmer, I want the system to monitor soil moisture continuously so that my crops receive water only when needed.{/td}
{td}When soil moisture drops below a set threshold, I want the system to automatically activate irrigation so I can avoid crop stress without being on-site.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}The system must continuously monitor air temperature and trigger heating or ventilation actuators when thresholds are exceeded.{/td}
{td}As a greenhouse operator, I want real-time temperature monitoring so that I can prevent crop damage from overheating or frost.{/td}
{td}When temperature falls below 10°C or exceeds 35°C, I want the system to activate heating or ventilation automatically so I can protect my crops without manual intervention.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}The system must monitor relative humidity at canopy level and activate humidification or ventilation actuators accordingly.{/td}
{td}As an operator, I want humidity levels tracked automatically so that I can prevent fungal diseases caused by excessive moisture.{/td}
{td}When humidity exceeds safe levels, I want the system to trigger ventilation so I can reduce disease risk without constant manual checks.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}The system should monitor CO₂ concentration and support controlled enrichment to optimize photosynthesis.{/td}
{td}As a greenhouse operator, I want CO₂ levels tracked so that I can optimize growing conditions and increase yield.{/td}
{td}When CO₂ drops below optimal levels, I want the system to alert me so I can adjust enrichment and improve crop productivity.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}The system should display live readings that refresh automatically without needing to reload the page.{/td}
{td}As a greenhouse operator, I want up-to-date readings on my screen so that I can catch problems as soon as they happen.{/td}
{td}When conditions change rapidly, I want the dashboard to refresh automatically so I can respond before crop damage occurs.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}The system should alert user when any reading goes outside the acceptable range.{/td}
{td}As a farmer, I want to receive a warning when conditions become dangerous so that I can act before my crops are damaged.{/td}
{td}When a parameter exceeds a safe range, I want an immediate alert so I can intervene before plants are stressed.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Automated Irrigation{/td}
{td}The system should allow operators to set irrigation schedules as a backup to sensor-based control.{/td}
{td}As a farmer, I want irrigation to follow a timed schedule so that my greenhouse can run for months without anyone on-site.{/td}
{td}When I am abroad for extended periods, I want a timed irrigation schedule to run autonomously so I can keep the greenhouse operational without being on-site.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Climate Control{/td}
{td}The system should allow operators to set acceptable ranges for temperature and humidity.{/td}
{td}As a farmer, I want to define my own comfort zones for the greenhouse so that the system reacts according to my specific crop needs.{/td}
{td}When I switch to a different crop, I want to reconfigure temperature and humidity ranges so I can adapt the system to new plant requirements.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td rowspan=2}Web Dashboard{/td}
{td}The system should have a web-based dashboard accessible from any browser without installing an app.{/td}
