{td rowspan=3}Soil and Water Management{/td}
{td}Soil moisture monitoring should be treated as the top priority across all greenhouse operations.{/td}
{td}As a farmer, I want soil moisture to be the first thing shown on my dashboard so that I always know if my crops need water.{/td}
{td}When opening the dashboard, I want soil moisture to appear prominently so I can immediately see if irrigation is needed.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}The system should support remote activation of irrigation from the website.{/td}
{td}As a greenhouse owner abroad, I want to start watering from my browser so that I can react to unexpected dry spells even when I am not in the country.{/td}
{td}When I am outside the country for weeks, I want to remotely activate irrigation from my browser so I can respond to unexpected dry spells.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}The system should prevent over-watering by stopping irrigation once the moisture level reaches the target.{/td}
{td}As a farmer, I want irrigation to stop automatically when the soil is wet enough so that I do not waste water or damage the roots.{/td}
{td}When soil reaches the target moisture level, I want irrigation to stop automatically so I can prevent over-watering and root damage.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Temperature and Humidity{/td}
